1
00:00:02,240 --> 00:00:03,840
I have to see for myself.

2
00:00:06,180 --> 00:00:08,650
(Episode 37)

3
00:00:10,150 --> 00:00:12,880
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

4
00:00:15,390 --> 00:00:16,820
Mom, watch this. Look!

5
00:00:28,830 --> 00:00:29,830
Welcome.

6
00:00:31,670 --> 00:00:34,740
Mom, do you have any idea
how expensive that jacket is?

7
00:00:34,810 --> 00:00:37,580
What if you get the ice cream on it?

8
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:39,710
Relax. It's not like
wearing it will ruin it.

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,480
- Right, Mom?
- You're right.

10
00:00:43,080 --> 00:00:46,480
It's so pretty.
Suk Hee loves sparkly things.

11
00:00:46,620 --> 00:00:47,720
Tae Pyung gave it to me.

12
00:00:47,950 --> 00:00:50,720
Mom! Take it off! Right now!

13
00:00:50,890 --> 00:00:53,430
- For crying out loud!
- Oh my, don't move.

14
00:00:55,160 --> 00:00:56,430
Give it here.

15
00:00:56,430 --> 00:00:58,900
I swear, I can't take this.

16
00:01:00,770 --> 00:01:02,770
- Honestly...
- It's okay.

17
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:09,640
I'm Kang Jun Ho.

18
00:01:10,180 --> 00:01:11,180
Let's meet.

19
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:13,480
Oh my.

20
00:01:14,180 --> 00:01:15,380
Yes!

21
00:01:15,710 --> 00:01:16,780
What a surprise.

22
00:01:51,980 --> 00:01:53,220
Hello? Dad?

23
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:57,920
Dad?

24
00:01:58,790 --> 00:02:00,230
Dad, what's wrong? Are you hurt?

25
00:02:03,060 --> 00:02:04,060
Jang Mi.

26
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:06,700
Listen to me carefully.

27
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:10,500
The one who did that to your mother...

28
00:02:13,170 --> 00:02:14,170
and you...

29
00:02:15,340 --> 00:02:16,340
You...

30
00:02:18,580 --> 00:02:19,580
Ssangkal...

31
00:02:57,180 --> 00:03:00,150
Dad! What's going on?

32
00:03:01,050 --> 00:03:03,590
Dad, what's wrong? Tell me.

33
00:03:04,460 --> 00:03:05,460
Dad!

34
00:03:17,270 --> 00:03:18,940
Oh Bok Gil and Oh Jang Mi...

35
00:03:18,940 --> 00:03:22,010
Why are those vermin so hard to kill?

36
00:03:22,270 --> 00:03:25,210
Those cockroaches!
Why won't they just die?

37
00:03:25,340 --> 00:03:28,610
Why?

38
00:03:28,610 --> 00:03:30,480
- Ma'am, calm down.
- Why?

39
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:33,220
- You need to calm down.
- Let go!

40
00:03:33,850 --> 00:03:36,620
Let go! Let me go!

41
00:03:36,690 --> 00:03:38,960
Hwa Young, stop it. That's enough.

42
00:03:41,690 --> 00:03:43,960
Hwa Young, take a deep breath.

43
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:45,500
Slowly.

44
00:04:16,030 --> 00:04:17,900
I'll take care of this. Don't worry.

45
00:04:19,430 --> 00:04:21,170
That bastard Oh Bok Gil...

46
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:25,040
was alive in the trunk.

47
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:29,440
I struck him with my own hands.

48
00:04:48,460 --> 00:04:49,460
It's okay.

49
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:52,500
I'm the one who did it all.

50
00:04:54,230 --> 00:04:55,230
It's okay.

51
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:57,900
Kang Hyuk.

52
00:05:06,540 --> 00:05:07,550
Thank you.

53
00:05:10,420 --> 00:05:11,420
I'm sorry.

54
00:05:20,490 --> 00:05:21,730
We're running out of time.

55
00:05:23,430 --> 00:05:25,700
Professor Kang should be
passing by here any second now.

56
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:29,330
- Really?
- Did you buy alcohol on your way here?

57
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:31,670
I bought a few bottles of soju.

58
00:05:32,870 --> 00:05:34,640
If he's not completely dead yet,

59
00:05:35,940 --> 00:05:37,180
it should be enough.

60
00:05:37,580 --> 00:05:38,810
Let's hurry and get ready.

61
00:05:54,190 --> 00:05:59,060
The person you're calling is unavailable.
Connecting to voicemail.

62
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,630
Why isn't the call going through
all of a sudden?

63
00:06:02,170 --> 00:06:03,230
Did his battery die?

64
00:06:03,970 --> 00:06:06,800
That's weird.
I could've sworn I heard him scream.

65
00:06:06,870 --> 00:06:08,770
Oh no, what if something happened to him?

66
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,070
What do I do?

67
00:06:12,010 --> 00:06:13,010
Jang Mi.

68
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:16,080
Tae Pyung,
I think something's happened to Dad.

69
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:18,150
What are you talking about?
What's wrong with Dad?

70
00:06:18,220 --> 00:06:21,390
I was just on the phone with him,
but now he's not picking up.

71
00:06:23,190 --> 00:06:27,390
He was gasping like he was in pain,
and I might've misheard,

72
00:06:27,690 --> 00:06:29,560
but I think I heard him scream.

73
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:31,030
What? A scream?

74
00:06:52,980 --> 00:06:56,320
Oh Bok Gil,
if you'd only kept your mouth shut,

75
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:58,120
none of this would have happened.

76
00:06:58,820 --> 00:07:02,590
You dug your own grave,
so don't you dare blame me!

77
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:14,040
Everything's set.

78
00:07:15,370 --> 00:07:16,870
When will Professor Kang Nam Bong
get here?

79
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,590
Hwa Young?

80
00:07:34,860 --> 00:07:36,290
When do you think you'll get here?

81
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:39,530
I'm almost there.
Probably in about ten minutes?

82
00:07:41,630 --> 00:07:43,200
Did you miss me already?

83
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:47,000
- I'll be waiting.
- Okay.

84
00:07:51,140 --> 00:07:53,480
I'll go park the car at the inn's lot.

85
00:08:01,620 --> 00:08:02,950
Don't look.

86
00:08:03,050 --> 00:08:04,460
You don't want to see this.

87
00:08:06,790 --> 00:08:07,830
All right.

88
00:08:09,330 --> 00:08:10,360
Kang Hyuk.

89
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:14,100
Once again, you're the only one I have.

90
00:08:17,030 --> 00:08:18,170
I'll go and take care of it.

91
00:08:44,330 --> 00:08:45,360
Oh Bok Gil.

92
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:48,430
Your life was cut short...

93
00:08:49,700 --> 00:08:53,070
because you just had to meddle
by taking in Jung Suk Hee and Oh Jang Mi.

94
00:08:53,910 --> 00:08:55,510
So don't you blame me.

95
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,840
I can check it myself.

96
00:09:31,940 --> 00:09:33,110
No.

97
00:09:33,110 --> 00:09:34,850
Back then, 30 years ago,

98
00:09:35,380 --> 00:09:38,380
I should have made absolutely sure
with my own two eyes.

99
00:09:40,020 --> 00:09:42,620
If I had,
then none of this would be happening now.

100
00:09:43,990 --> 00:09:44,990
I apologize.

101
00:10:24,300 --> 00:10:25,600
Oh, no...

102
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:01,800
Is that...

103
00:11:02,030 --> 00:11:03,070
Is that a person?

104
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,670
Still no word from Dad?

105
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:08,470
Tae Sook, where did Dad go?

106
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:11,410
He didn't say where he was going.

107
00:11:11,410 --> 00:11:13,480
He took a lunchbox
and some side dishes and left.

108
00:11:13,710 --> 00:11:16,180
And his phone's off. This is so strange.

109
00:11:16,180 --> 00:11:17,880
I really hope he's okay.

110
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:20,990
Dad asked for CEO Chae's number earlier.

111
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:22,290
You think he went to see her?

112
00:11:22,350 --> 00:11:25,190
No. If he went there, why would he scream?

113
00:11:25,190 --> 00:11:26,890
- That makes no sense!
- I guess you're right.

114
00:11:27,460 --> 00:11:30,130
He said he was just going to call her
for a customer follow-up.

115
00:11:30,190 --> 00:11:33,160
Maybe his phone's dead?

116
00:11:33,260 --> 00:11:37,540
He should be back by now.
Dad's never done this before.

117
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:41,010
- What if something happened to him?
- I can't just wait around.

118
00:11:49,810 --> 00:11:51,180
Yes, this is Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

119
00:11:51,250 --> 00:11:53,250
Baek Ho,
you have to help me find my father.

120
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:57,220
Tae Pyung, what are you talking about?

121
00:11:57,590 --> 00:11:59,090
What do you mean
by helping you find your father?

122
00:12:12,970 --> 00:12:15,370
Seriously, what is happening?

123
00:12:32,090 --> 00:12:33,090
No...

124
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:41,730
No way...

125
00:12:45,670 --> 00:12:47,340
Excuse me? Hello?

126
00:12:49,570 --> 00:12:51,740
(Oh Jang Mi)

127
00:12:56,350 --> 00:12:57,850
Hey, can you hear me?

128
00:12:58,580 --> 00:13:00,480
Hey!

129
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:02,420
He reeks of alcohol.

130
00:13:03,990 --> 00:13:06,190
Smells like he bathed in alcohol.

131
00:13:06,620 --> 00:13:08,030
And of all the cars, it had to be mine.

132
00:13:11,660 --> 00:13:12,660
Oh my...

133
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:17,600
What?

134
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:26,180
What was that?

135
00:13:30,510 --> 00:13:32,250
The person you're calling is unavailable.

136
00:13:32,820 --> 00:13:35,490
- CEO Chae isn't picking up either.
- Why would she? It's late at night.

137
00:13:36,550 --> 00:13:39,860
- She's probably at home resting.
- But if Dad didn't go see CEO Chae,

138
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,230
then what happened to him?

139
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:02,980
Yes, Hwa Young.

140
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:05,850
Professor.

141
00:14:06,150 --> 00:14:08,790
I must have dozed off
while waiting for you.

142
00:14:09,420 --> 00:14:12,720
But you said you'd be here in ten minutes.
Why aren't you here yet?

143
00:14:13,460 --> 00:14:16,160
- Where are you right now?
- About that...

144
00:14:17,830 --> 00:14:22,600
- Did something happen?
- Hwa Young, don't panic.

145
00:14:23,270 --> 00:14:26,670
- I think I've caused an accident.
- An accident?

146
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:28,270
On my way over...

147
00:14:29,940 --> 00:14:32,510
- I think I hit someone.
- What?

148
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:37,480
- So, are they dead?
- No, I think he's still alive.

149
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:39,820
He just opened his eyes for a second,

150
00:14:39,820 --> 00:14:41,920
and I think he's trying to say something.

151
00:14:42,120 --> 00:14:44,990
No. What is he trying to say?

152
00:14:45,290 --> 00:14:50,230
This pest just won't die.
Why won't he just die already?

153
00:14:51,460 --> 00:14:53,460
He can't tell him that I did that to him.

154
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:54,800
Hey, sir!

155
00:14:57,170 --> 00:14:58,670
- What are you saying?
- Professor!

156
00:14:58,670 --> 00:14:59,700
Wait.

157
00:14:59,770 --> 00:15:01,970
I think he's trying to say something.
Hold on.

158
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:03,740
What sense could a drunk person make?

159
00:15:05,140 --> 00:15:06,140
What?

160
00:15:06,140 --> 00:15:09,150
Did I say he looked drunk?

161
00:15:12,450 --> 00:15:13,520
It's obvious, isn't it?

162
00:15:14,450 --> 00:15:16,990
A person who couldn't even dodge a car
this late at night...

163
00:15:22,330 --> 00:15:24,300
So what are you going to do, Professor?

164
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:31,840
Chef Kang!

165
00:15:32,340 --> 00:15:34,670
- Are you still here?
- I was just about to leave.

166
00:15:35,870 --> 00:15:37,410
You said you wanted to see me.

167
00:15:37,910 --> 00:15:40,440
Oh my goodness. Were you waiting for me?

168
00:15:41,110 --> 00:15:44,010
I knew you couldn't resist me forever.

169
00:15:44,010 --> 00:15:45,450
Let me be blunt.

170
00:15:46,780 --> 00:15:49,450
Did you pester CEO Chae
about promoting me?

171
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:50,920
No.

172
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:53,890
Take a guess.

173
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:55,760
I'm not kidding.

174
00:15:56,060 --> 00:15:57,330
Neither am I.

175
00:15:58,200 --> 00:16:00,030
I'm telling you,
this is a huge step for us.

176
00:16:00,330 --> 00:16:03,170
So you just wanted an excuse for a date.

177
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:04,300
Right, Jun Ho?

178
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:06,640
I'm all for it! Anytime.

179
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:07,870
Stop flattering yourself.

180
00:16:08,770 --> 00:16:12,010
I'm debating whether or not
to accept the promotion.

181
00:16:13,110 --> 00:16:14,980
I wanted to confirm with you
before I make my decision.

182
00:16:14,980 --> 00:16:17,720
What's there to think about?
Of course you should take it.

183
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:19,280
That answer seems sufficient.

184
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:23,420
It's clear
you had nothing to do with my promotion.

185
00:16:25,060 --> 00:16:26,060
Well then, get home safe.

186
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:28,160
What? You're just leaving?

187
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:30,590
Then at least take me home, Kang Jun Ho!

188
00:16:38,870 --> 00:16:41,440
You just came from the restaurant again?

189
00:16:42,540 --> 00:16:44,810
Oh dear. Is it because
you’re stressed about it?

190
00:16:45,110 --> 00:16:48,550
- No.
- It's written all over your face.

191
00:16:50,150 --> 00:16:51,150
Have some fruit.

192
00:16:53,920 --> 00:16:57,820
- Is no one else home yet?
- Baek Ho already left again.

193
00:16:58,220 --> 00:17:00,260
I swear, he can never stay put.

194
00:17:01,460 --> 00:17:04,160
What's the point of me
talking to Oh Jang Mi's father?

195
00:17:04,290 --> 00:17:06,560
Has Dad not come home yet?

196
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:09,870
Your dad is going through
a mid-life crisis.

197
00:17:10,870 --> 00:17:14,870
When I talk to him, he's in his own world
and barely hears a word I say.

198
00:17:16,110 --> 00:17:18,480
Oh dear. This is what getting old is like.

199
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:22,450
So, while you're still young,

200
00:17:22,710 --> 00:17:26,250
you should date around, find someone nice,
and think about settling down.

201
00:17:26,850 --> 00:17:29,120
Youth is fleeting, you know.

202
00:17:32,590 --> 00:17:35,260
Has your father not come home yet?
Has he been in touch?

203
00:17:36,030 --> 00:17:37,060
No.

204
00:17:37,060 --> 00:17:39,960
I hope nothing's wrong with him.

205
00:17:40,460 --> 00:17:43,200
This is not good.
We need to call the police now.

206
00:17:43,270 --> 00:17:44,270
Jang Mi.

207
00:17:44,570 --> 00:17:46,000
The police
won’t file a missing adult report...

208
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,500
until they’ve been gone for 24 hours.

209
00:17:47,870 --> 00:17:49,810
Let me try calling Detective Kim first.

210
00:17:55,380 --> 00:17:56,810
Oh my.

211
00:17:56,810 --> 00:17:58,380
Hello? Dad?

212
00:18:02,420 --> 00:18:03,420
Detective Kim.

213
00:18:14,060 --> 00:18:16,370
Ms. Oh Jang Mi,
you need to get to the ER right now.

214
00:18:16,730 --> 00:18:18,370
Your father's been in a car accident.

215
00:18:39,290 --> 00:18:41,090
Dad!

216
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:45,530
Excuse me, the patient from the accident,
Mr. Oh Bok Gil. Where is he?

217
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:48,230
He's getting an emergency CT scan
right now.

218
00:18:48,230 --> 00:18:50,370
The doctor will be out
to speak with you shortly.

219
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,070
A car accident?

220
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:54,710
How could this happen to Dad?

221
00:18:55,110 --> 00:18:56,910
What's going to happen to my dad?

222
00:18:57,570 --> 00:18:58,680
I'm sure he'll be okay.

223
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:03,980
Excuse me, are you
Mr. Oh Bok Gil's family?

224
00:19:04,180 --> 00:19:07,180
Yes, he's our dad. How is he?

225
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:09,050
He has severe head trauma.

226
00:19:09,350 --> 00:19:11,120
He has an open skull fracture
on the back of his head,

227
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:13,160
and there was significant blood loss.

228
00:19:14,830 --> 00:19:17,790
We need to rush him into emergency surgery
right now.

229
00:19:20,460 --> 00:19:21,470
Dad!

230
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:24,840
- Dad!
- Dad!

231
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:26,670
Dad, please open your eyes.

232
00:19:27,070 --> 00:19:28,170
Dad!

233
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:31,210
Dad, please, just open your eyes.

234
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:33,880
Dad.

235
00:19:33,940 --> 00:19:35,510
(Operating Center)

236
00:19:35,580 --> 00:19:37,780
- Dad, I'll be praying for you, okay?
- Dad.

237
00:19:37,780 --> 00:19:40,180
I'll be praying for you, Dad.

238
00:19:41,490 --> 00:19:44,050
Jang Mi, let's let the doctors
handle it for now.

239
00:19:44,290 --> 00:19:46,560
Your father will get through the surgery
just fine.

240
00:19:48,890 --> 00:19:50,030
Please.

241
00:19:50,590 --> 00:19:53,100
Please, save my dad.

242
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:55,500
My good, sweet dad.

243
00:19:56,230 --> 00:20:00,400
There's still so much
I wanted to do for him.

244
00:20:01,270 --> 00:20:04,640
There's so much
I regret not doing for him.

245
00:20:05,380 --> 00:20:06,710
What am I going to do?

246
00:20:07,010 --> 00:20:08,010
Jang Mi.

247
00:20:09,010 --> 00:20:10,450
- Dad.
- Come on, get up.

248
00:20:15,450 --> 00:20:16,450
Dad.

249
00:20:19,190 --> 00:20:21,120
What am I going to do?

250
00:20:26,360 --> 00:20:30,470
(Operating Center)

251
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:33,300
Dad.

252
00:20:50,150 --> 00:20:51,520
What? Surgery?

253
00:20:52,660 --> 00:20:54,490
Then the doctors could find out...

254
00:20:54,490 --> 00:20:56,530
he was hit on the head
before the accident.

255
00:20:56,590 --> 00:20:59,860
True, but they might just assume
the car accident caused it.

256
00:21:01,630 --> 00:21:02,900
Did you hide it well?

257
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:04,200
The wrench, I mean.

258
00:21:05,340 --> 00:21:08,570
What is she talking about?
Hiding a wrench this early in the morning?

259
00:21:13,510 --> 00:21:14,950
(Detective Team Two)

260
00:21:16,310 --> 00:21:18,280
So what are you going to do, Professor?

261
00:21:21,790 --> 00:21:23,720
I'm not sure.

262
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:24,890
To be honest,

263
00:21:25,760 --> 00:21:28,530
I was planning to run away like a coward.

264
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:30,760
But your call...

265
00:21:32,430 --> 00:21:34,360
snapped me out of it.

266
00:21:34,770 --> 00:21:36,470
Are you going to report this?

267
00:21:37,270 --> 00:21:41,200
This person was completely drunk,
just lying in the middle of the road.

268
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:43,910
He seems to be alive,
so I need to call an ambulance now.

269
00:21:44,210 --> 00:21:48,810
- I wonder if they'll be quick out here.
- What? An ambulance?

270
00:21:50,250 --> 00:21:53,220
But what if he's already dead?

271
00:21:54,420 --> 00:21:55,420
What?

272
00:21:59,290 --> 00:22:02,060
We just heard from the hospital.

273
00:22:02,060 --> 00:22:03,530
The victim, Mr. Oh Bok Gil,

274
00:22:03,830 --> 00:22:05,460
was just taken into surgery.

275
00:22:05,730 --> 00:22:06,830
That's a relief.

276
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:09,900
- That means he's not dead.
- But, by any chance,

277
00:22:10,270 --> 00:22:14,340
after you hit Mr. Oh Bok Gil,
did you notice anything unusual?

278
00:22:16,670 --> 00:22:18,340
He was lying on the road.

279
00:22:19,310 --> 00:22:20,640
And he reeked of alcohol.

280
00:22:21,210 --> 00:22:22,280
Are you sure about that?

281
00:22:24,920 --> 00:22:26,050
Mr. Kang Nam Bong.

282
00:22:26,580 --> 00:22:28,890
What were you doing out there
at that hour?

283
00:22:29,590 --> 00:22:32,790
What if the police ask you
what you were doing there?

284
00:22:33,360 --> 00:22:34,390
I promise...

285
00:22:36,290 --> 00:22:38,960
I'll make sure
you're not implicated in this.

286
00:22:39,230 --> 00:22:40,260
So...

287
00:22:41,030 --> 00:22:43,430
let's not contact each other for a while.

288
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:49,310
A resort I previously consulted for
was nearby.

289
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:51,780
I was on my way there.

290
00:22:52,110 --> 00:22:53,310
At that hour?

291
00:22:53,710 --> 00:22:56,080
A few days ago, I tried to go there
but got lost.

292
00:22:56,710 --> 00:22:58,780
My teaching assistant gave me directions,

293
00:22:59,220 --> 00:23:01,020
and it was on my mind, so I decided to go.

294
00:23:01,020 --> 00:23:02,390
You can ask my teaching assistant.

295
00:23:04,090 --> 00:23:05,490
Yes, I see.

296
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,660
Please give us your statement
about the accident.

297
00:23:08,560 --> 00:23:12,330
Someone was lying in the road.
I slammed the brakes, but it was too late.

298
00:23:13,330 --> 00:23:17,900
On that dark, secluded road,
I never imagined anyone would be there.

299
00:23:18,970 --> 00:23:21,300
Lying in the middle of the road?

300
00:23:21,940 --> 00:23:22,940
Yes.

301
00:23:24,310 --> 00:23:28,910
The thought of a drunk person
on a dark country road with no lights...

302
00:23:29,350 --> 00:23:30,850
is just unimaginable.

303
00:23:30,850 --> 00:23:33,650
The investigation will sort that out.

304
00:23:35,350 --> 00:23:36,750
For now, Mr. Kang Nam Bong,

305
00:23:37,250 --> 00:23:40,420
- you're charged with negligent driving.
- I see.

306
00:23:41,490 --> 00:23:44,630
But of course, I didn't do it on purpose.

307
00:23:44,690 --> 00:23:47,460
The victim is in very critical condition
right now.

308
00:23:48,330 --> 00:23:50,030
He might not make it,

309
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:52,970
so you'd be wise to get a lawyer.

310
00:24:00,340 --> 00:24:01,580
Okay, I got it. I'll be right there.

311
00:24:01,580 --> 00:24:02,610
Honey.

312
00:24:03,080 --> 00:24:05,650
Don't say a single word until I get there.

313
00:24:05,650 --> 00:24:06,680
Okay.

314
00:24:07,350 --> 00:24:08,350
Mom.

315
00:24:10,720 --> 00:24:13,960
- Jun Ho, I don't know what to do.
- What's wrong?

316
00:24:14,020 --> 00:24:15,760
Your father was in a car accident...

317
00:24:16,230 --> 00:24:17,630
and hit someone.

318
00:24:17,630 --> 00:24:18,660
What?

319
00:24:19,030 --> 00:24:20,030
Dad did?

320
00:24:21,830 --> 00:24:25,540
- I'll go with you.
- No. You're up for a promotion.

321
00:24:25,740 --> 00:24:28,770
You can't just skip work.
Hurry and get ready.

322
00:24:28,840 --> 00:24:30,840
What about Baek Ho?
Mom, take Baek Ho with you.

323
00:24:30,840 --> 00:24:33,140
He's out helping a friend's father
with something.

324
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:36,410
- Try not to worry, Mom.
- I'll be back soon.

325
00:24:41,320 --> 00:24:44,890
Professor Kang is being investigated
for negligent injury in a car accident.

326
00:24:46,360 --> 00:24:49,560
Why is Oh Jang Mi's father
so hard to kill?

327
00:24:50,230 --> 00:24:54,400
If he survives and opens his mouth,
we're screwed.

328
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:56,830
His life is hanging by a thread,
so please don't worry too much.

329
00:24:57,570 --> 00:25:01,240
- It's too soon to be pessimistic.
- Keep a close watch on him.

330
00:25:02,540 --> 00:25:05,340
If the worst happens, we'll have to act.
What choice do we have?

331
00:25:05,680 --> 00:25:07,310
Yes, don't you worry.

332
00:25:12,150 --> 00:25:14,420
What if he wakes up?

333
00:25:15,520 --> 00:25:16,990
That absolutely cannot happen.

334
00:25:17,590 --> 00:25:19,760
He must die.

335
00:25:30,230 --> 00:25:32,800
CEO Chae, why the long face?

336
00:25:32,900 --> 00:25:36,070
You came in so late last night.
You must be exhausted from overworking.

337
00:25:36,510 --> 00:25:41,180
She works so hard that she looks awful,
Chairman.

338
00:25:42,310 --> 00:25:44,050
Shit, this is so annoying.

339
00:25:45,150 --> 00:25:47,550
Grandpa, how do I look?

340
00:25:47,650 --> 00:25:50,620
What do you mean?
Of course you're the prettiest, Seo Rin.

341
00:25:51,590 --> 00:25:52,860
It's annoying.

342
00:25:52,860 --> 00:25:55,190
People say I look like someone.

343
00:25:55,190 --> 00:25:58,800
Yesterday, some creepy old guy told me
I look just like his daughter.

344
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:00,030
Shit.

345
00:26:01,100 --> 00:26:03,830
They only say that
because you're so pretty.

346
00:26:03,900 --> 00:26:06,600
They probably meant you look like
a movie star or something.

347
00:26:08,870 --> 00:26:12,210
I'm going to focus on figuring out
how to win Jun Ho over.

348
00:26:13,010 --> 00:26:16,580
Mom, are you dying or something?

349
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:18,520
What?

350
00:26:18,620 --> 00:26:21,150
Is that why you're suddenly telling me
to go for it with Jun Ho?

351
00:26:21,350 --> 00:26:24,620
Oh my, you told her to go for it
with Jun Ho?

352
00:26:24,690 --> 00:26:26,560
What's the meaning of this?

353
00:26:27,020 --> 00:26:29,090
After being so against it,

354
00:26:29,560 --> 00:26:32,160
- why the sudden change of heart?
- It's not like that, Father.

355
00:26:32,530 --> 00:26:36,200
I just felt I was too hard on Seo Rin
for her crush.

356
00:26:36,570 --> 00:26:38,340
It's not like they're getting married,

357
00:26:38,340 --> 00:26:40,040
Chef Kang Jun Ho is capable...

358
00:26:40,040 --> 00:26:42,940
and his family is decent,
so I’ll see how things go.

359
00:26:42,940 --> 00:26:46,740
Seo Rin is the heir
who will lead our company, Dream.

360
00:26:47,010 --> 00:26:50,280
Fine, you can date him.
But you can never, ever marry that punk.

361
00:26:51,380 --> 00:26:54,020
Grandpa, you don't really know my Jun Ho.

362
00:26:54,550 --> 00:26:58,590
Mom. You've finally seen Jun Ho's worth,
haven't you?

363
00:26:58,860 --> 00:27:00,890
That's why
you gave me your blessing, right?

364
00:27:01,890 --> 00:27:03,330
Something like that.

365
00:27:27,380 --> 00:27:29,650
By the way, Mom, did your car break down?

366
00:27:31,150 --> 00:27:32,160
What?

367
00:27:32,160 --> 00:27:34,160
I heard you mention a wrench.

368
00:27:35,090 --> 00:27:36,090
What?

369
00:27:36,560 --> 00:27:38,630
"Did you hide it well?
The wrench, I mean."

370
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:40,200
That's what you said, Mom.

371
00:27:43,630 --> 00:27:45,100
What are you talking about?

372
00:27:53,640 --> 00:27:55,380
The surgery went well,

373
00:27:56,280 --> 00:27:57,910
but we need to monitor his progress.

374
00:27:59,620 --> 00:28:00,650
Tonight...

375
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:02,650
could be critical.

376
00:28:24,140 --> 00:28:25,840
(The First Man)

377
00:28:26,140 --> 00:28:27,840
Don't even think about
seeing Kang Baek Ho again.

378
00:28:28,110 --> 00:28:31,750
Kang Baek Ho's father is the suspect
who hit Dad with a car.

379
00:28:31,850 --> 00:28:32,850
What?

380
00:28:33,050 --> 00:28:37,190
But why does Mom keep lying?
What's the big deal with that wrench?

381
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:39,760
First, I need to put the screws
to Manager Lee.

382
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:42,660
I'm Detective Kim Hyun Soo,
Yeongseo Police Department.

383
00:28:42,660 --> 00:28:44,860
You know Mr. Kang Nam Bong
and Mr. Oh Bok Gil, right?

384
00:28:44,890 --> 00:28:46,260
What's this about?

385
00:28:46,830 --> 00:28:48,830
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
